We were greeted by open garbage in the lower floor "lobby", scaffolding and ladders and other dangerous items, poor directions to the 2nd floor where the registration desk is found.	I wanted to sign something - but they wouldn't help me, and the screaming was more than we were willing to listen to... Our safety was more important to us.... it was worth LEAVING.	As a woman traveling alone, I felt very safe and I found the neighborhood to be more affordable and less trafficky than others I visited in Rome.	This sometimes makes it difficult to find a decent, well priced and safe place to stay, especially if you are a female travelling alone.